>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1269<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/02 2:15 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ENRAGED - on a RAMPAGE</span><hr size=1> ENRAGE = furious discipline, mobs will do this when they go below 10% health, effect is auto-riposting every attack made from the front arch.<br>
<br>
Response: Attack off if you are in his front arch<br>
<br>
RAMPAGE = Proc that makes the mob have a round of attacks on someone other than the person currently holding top spot on aggro list.<br>
<br>
Response: If you are attacked right after a RAMPAGE, then /gu &lt;&lt; MYNAME == RAMPAGED &gt;&gt; -- you will need heals <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19405 target=blank>Marshall Sscaley Iceblade</a><br><i><a href=http://companions.windsofstorm.net>The Companions ~ Team Headstart</a></i> <br>
Overlizard on Tribunal</big><br><small>"Tails are not for biting or pulling!"</small></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilzalot>Kilzalot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/02 4:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ENRAGED - on a RAMPAGE</span><hr size=1> Little more on Rampage.  Lots of times when you have a rampage mob like say Vindi, the raid will define one person to try and get on &quot;ramps&quot; so they can make it a tank class instead of one of the healers taking damage.  Have the monk pull, FD close to the camp area.  Rampage tank tags with an arrow or 2 and when the mob gets to camp the MT engages and takes aggro.  A few seconds after the MT engages then the RT goes.  Then the MT can call mellee engage when he feels he has aggro.  &quot;Ramps&quot; should be setup on the rampage tank now. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=132589">Veteran Kilzalot Drachonis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
