<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=335271">Rubik Dashammybot</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilzadikandinsky>KilzadiKandinsky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/02 4:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ENRAGED - on a RAMPAGE</span><hr size=1> On Enrage: if you are on the side of the mob he will still riposte your attacks but not hit you. i'd stay behind the mob at all times when you're not MT. most mobs 56+ Enrage<br>
<br>
On Rampage: this is such a fun skill that mobs have. it has a HUGE range too, i was rampaged 1/2 way across a zone once.<br>
<br>
later you'll encounter Flurry, anotehr nasty skill which is a free melee round on the person highest on the aggro list. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bombair>Bombair</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/02 5:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   enrage...</span><hr size=1> Just a suggestion to add on the response on ENRAGE...<br>
<br>
Typically I favor ducking instead of simply turning attack off...<br>
<br>
If your fighting a heavy hitting mob this can be a problem...you run a high risk of repositeing. Which is taking more damage than you need to be. I've seen several times where thats all it took added in with the damage the mob is already doing to finish off a tank. Ducking stops all of your melee and will help prevent this.<br>
<br>
You will start looking forward to enrage at one point.. Just to see whos afk and watch a few rangers die.<br>
<br>
Then again...You will have those idiotic moments where mobs spawn when pets die and its not so funny. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
